'''Russian State Film and Photo Archive''' ({{lang-ru|Российский государственный архив кинофотодокументов}}), also known as '''Russian State Documentary Film and Photo Archive''', or '''Krasnogorsk Archive''', or simply '''RGAKFD''' ({{lang-ru|РГАКФД}}), is an archive of documentary newsreels and photographs located at [[Krasnogorsk, Moscow Oblast|Krasnogorsk]], [[Moscow Oblast]], [[Russia]]. The archive contains more than 1 million photos and has a virtually complete collection of newsreels from 1919 to 1985 that documents the political, military and other diverse episodes of the [[USSR]].
